{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "We assume that each of the |θ s,p ⟩ states have already been prepared.",
    "The rotations are enacted by, for each s = 0,..., m -1, swapping (\"injecting\") the correct |θ s,p ⟩ state with the sth data qubit.",
    "Exactly one θ s,p will be injected for each s. Since (0, 0) is the only (s, p) with s = 0, the first step is to swap |θ 0,0 ⟩ with the first data qubit.",
    "The second step is to, conditioned on the first data register being |1⟩, swap the registers holding |θ 1,0 ⟩ and |θ 1,1 ⟩, and then inject the register originally holding |θ 1,0 ⟩ into the second data register (using a swap gate).",
    "In general, the sth rotation is enacted by first swapping the correct |θ s,p ⟩ to the top of the size-2 s register initially holding the states |θ s,p ⟩, and then swapping the top register into the sth data qubit."
  ],
